#
# When/if this is revisited, write a new task in awx-integration that PATCHes
# the InstanceGroup directly via the AWX API. Do NOT re-enable this fragment.
#
# SAME BLIND SPOT — job concurrency (WP1S Phase 3, single-node fit):
# `max_concurrent_jobs` and `max_forks` are fields on the InstanceGroup /
# ContainerGroup, NOT AWX Django settings — so they CANNOT be set via
# extra_settings (SCHEDULE_MAX_JOBS / DEFAULT_EXECUTION_QUEUE_MAX_CONCURRENT_JOBS
# are not real AWX settings; verified against AWX 24.6 docs 2026-05-29). The
# per-job fork ceiling we CAN set globally is MAX_FORKS (a real Django setting,
# wired above via awx_max_forks). A true concurrency cap would also need the
